i  Monastic: 		gopher.black	70
i  "This philosophy attempts to maximize deep efforts by		gopher.black	70
i  eliminating or radically minimizing shallow obligations."		gopher.black	70
i  — isolate yourself for long periods of time without		gopher.black	70
i  distractions; no shallow work allowed. 		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i  Bimodal: 		gopher.black	70
i  "This philosophy asks that you divide your time, dedicating some		gopher.black	70
i  clearly defined stretches to deep pursuits and leaving the rest		gopher.black	70
i  open to everything else." – dedicate a few consecutive days		gopher.black	70
i  (like weekends, or a Sunday, for example) for deep work only, at		gopher.black	70
i  least one day a week.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i  Rhythmic: 		gopher.black	70
i  "This philosophy argues that the easiest way to consistently		gopher.black	70
i  start deep work sessions is to transform them into a simple		gopher.black	70
i  regular habit." – create a daily habit of three to four hours		gopher.black	70
i  every day to perform deep work on your project.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
i  Journalistic: 		gopher.black	70
i  "in which you fit deep work wherever you can into your		gopher.black	70
i  schedule." — Not recommended to try out first, since you first		gopher.black	70
i  need to accustom yourself to deep work.		gopher.black	70
